<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 635px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Operations Activities</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>The design and construction team should prepare for operation of the facility, including the <strong>initial and extended periods of aftercare</strong>, based on the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>Conduct aftercare review meetings and workshops</li>
<li>Record user comments related to functionality and effectiveness</li>
<li>Maintain records of site walks to detect emerging issues</li>
<li>Fine-tune the building services engineering systems</li>
<li>Fine-tune the structural monitoring and control systems</li>
<li>Record and feedback details of all fine-tuning</li>
<li>Update the asset information model (AIM)</li>
<li>Update the facility handbook</li>
<li>Update the facility user guide</li>
</ol>
<p>The Lead Appointed Party, operator, operations team or facility manager should <strong>prepare for operation of the asset/facility</strong>, including the initial and extended periods of aftercare, based on the following activities:</p>
<ol>
<li>Record and review <strong>early energy usage for comparison</strong> with predictions</li>
<li>Review and record <strong>Building Management System (BMS) monitoring</strong> of environmental conditions to detect any emerging problems</li>
<li>Set up a <strong>helpdesk with a physical presence</strong>
</li>
<li>Prepare and circulate newsletters or utilize other media for <strong>communicating directly with end-users</strong>
</li>
</ol></div></div></div></div></div></div>